// Regression: libFuzzer, 2026-04-17. Malformed struct field declaration like
// `float3 per.uv = float2(...)` (dot-accessor used as a field name) drove
// ParseStruct's field loop into an infinite allocation loop: Synchronize()
// could advance without making the loop state change, so each iteration
// pushed new field-parsing allocations without progress.
// Fix: progress guard in ParseStruct's field loop (bwsl_parser_soa.cpp),
// same pattern as the ParseEnum variant loop.
// Expected: compiler exits cleanly with a parse error, not a hang.
pipeline P {
    struct S {
        float3 a.b = float3(0.0);
    };
}
